CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 12, 1969, pg. 11 reads: "Testimonial Banquet - Ruth Temple 116, IBPOE of W., recently sponsored a Testimonial Banquet honoring Past Grand Daughter Ruler Catherine P. Johnson. The affair was held at the Greater Pittsburgh Lodge 115 on Lincoln Ave.  Pictured with the honoree are: Clara N. Randolph, PGDR; Eli Randolph, PGER; J. Amos Harris, President of Penna. State Association of Philadelphia and PGER; Nadie Jordan, PGDR; Col. Samuel Gray, Lucille Elliott, Dr. Ruler and PGDR; William E. Johnson PSP State Esquire, Fred Montgomery, Chief Cntler; Helen Saunders, PGDR of Steelton, Pa. Ellis Gaither, Exalted Ruler; Laura Randall, Director of Civil Liberties of Harrisburg; Dr. Laffette Savis, Director of Education, Hester R. Thomas, State President, and of course Dt. Catherine Johnson, PDGR and Director of Education. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven women and six men, including Clara N. Randolph, Eli Randolph, J. Amos Harris, Nadie Jordan, Col. Samuel Gray, Lucille Elliott, William E. Johnson, Fred Montgomery, left end; Helen Saunders, Ellis Gaither, Laura Randall, Dr. Laffette Savis, Hester R. Thomas, and Dt. Catherine Johnson, gathered behind rectangular banquet table in Greater Pittsburgh Lodge 115, Lincoln Avenue for testimonial banquet
